@node "intro" "I.Introduction"

 WBWort is a game of spelling words, like Scrabble.
 Most functions are easy to understand, so you won't have to 
 read the whole guide. 

 @{i}Don't say does not look nice, until you've tried
 the new preferences option! @{ui} ;)
 
 That' all you need to know, I think...

 As long as this copy is unregistered some boring requesters
 will appear (To stop this ... @{"register" link "regis"}). This is
 no cripple-ware, there are no limitations on unregistered versions.

 If you have any problems with this piece of software or if you
 find any bugs, write to this address ----> @{"author" link "autho"}.

 You don't have to register for this, but I've spent so much time
 on this program... I think it's worth some money.

 Enjoy it!

 @{b}REQUIREMENTS:@{ub}

 Kick 3.x
 68020 or better recommended for using computer opponent. 
 
 The Vocabulary Editor needs @{"MUI" link VocEd.guide/MUI}. 

@endnode

