@node "instr" "IV.Instructions"

 @{b} Starting WBWort @{ub}

 WBWort will try to open it's windows on the workbench. 
 If this is impossible, you may start with 'emergency preferences', 
 which means that WBW starts on an hires-laced screen 
 and uses topaz.font (size 8 pixels). 

 Then you can change the @{"display preferences" link "prefs"}.

 @{b} Starting a new game @{ub}

 Pick the menu game/new to start a new game. A @{"game preferences" link "gameprefs"}
 requester will appear. Choose your opponent and language  and 
 click on the ok-button.

 Both players get eight letters, the player with the lowest first letter 
 begins. Click on your letters to choose one, it moves to the right,
 then you can place it at another position in your set of letters or on the
 field. 

 The first letter must also be the first letter of the word you
 want to place on the board. Following letters must be placed one by one
 to the right of or below this starting point.

 If you have finished your turn, click on the symbol right under your
 name. If you can't spell any word choose the menu turn/pass, or exchange
 some of your letters with turn/change.

 If you don't want to play anymore, select Game/quit, do not turn
 your computer off, or no changes will be saved.

@endnode

@node "rules" "V.Rules""

 Each player gets eight letters. The player with the lowest first letter starts.
 He if he can build a word with his letters, he puts them down on the
 field including the center field. Next player's free to place his word
 anywhere on the field, but it must have contact to another word. If
 his word builds a new word by extending an already placed word, both words
 count as new words. All letters count different points. If they're placed
 on fields labeld '2*B' or '3*B' they're points will be multiplied by 2 or 3.
 'x*W' Fields mean that the points of the whole word will be multiplied.
 Blank letters can be used as a 'joker' for any letter, but they don't count
 any points.

 If a player can use all eight letters, while there are still new ones
 available, he get's 50 extra points.

 You can exchange a blank, that is already placed on the board, with the
 letter, for which it stands. To do this, select this letter and then
 click on the blank.
 
@endnode

@node "extra" "VI.Extras"

 1. Statistics
 If you pick the menu Info/Statistics, you can see who has
 placed the longest word and so on. Passing and exchanging letters
 count as 0 points, exchanging a blank does not count for the
 statistics. Choose the diagram to see the development through
 the whole game.

 2. Save ASCII-FILE
 This function will create an ASCII-file of the current situation,
 it' quite useless, but perhaps you're so proud of the game, that
 you want to print it. Of course you can't reload these files
 as saved games.

 3. Vocabulary Editor <VocEd>
 To remove words from the vocabulary or to type in new ones,
 use the Vocabulary Editor by @{"Sascha Werth" link "sascha"}.
 You can click on words to change them or add new ones by typing
 them into the input line. 

 @{b}You can't change the vocabulary, while WBWort is running!@{ub}

 WBW saves the vocabulary if you quit, your changes, made with VocEd
 will be overwritten.

 See @{"VocEd.guide" link VocEd.guide/main} for more information.

@endnode


