@node "gameprefs" "Game Preferences"

 The preferences requester:

 @{b}1. Computer opponent @{ub}

 The normal computer opponent tries to get the highest
 score out of a turn, the <easy> opponent tries to place
 the longest word.

 @{b}2. Minimum length @{ub}

 Some people play this game without words of two letters.

 @{b}3. Letter distribution and vocabulary @{ub}

 Select the distribution used in your country and
 a vocabulary of your language.
 By now, english, german, swedish and french are available,
 other languages will be added.

@endnode

@node "prefs" "Display Preferences"

 @{b}Graphics  @{ub

   - You may change the whole look of the board and letters
     here. Each graphics set is represented by one file in
     the 'WBWort/Des' directory. The name of the selected
     file, a short descripton and a preview is displayed.
     Some graphic sets are too large for small screens (e.g.
     'newton.des'. WBW will have problems if you select
     a small screen but large graphics. See @{"Problems with Prefs" link emergency} 
     for more information. 

  -  If you want to know more about the new graphic files 
     or draw an own one, click here: @{"Graphic files" link graphics}.
 
 @{b}Fonts  @{ub}

  -  You can change the two fonts WBW uses.

      The @{b}Gadget Font@{ub} is used for all Gadgets (Buttons,
      Cycles, String input etc.)

      The @{b}Text@{ub} is used for all text display (labels etc.)

     WBW will have problems if you select a small screen but
     large fonts. See @{"Problems with Prefs" link emergency} for more 
     information. 

 @{b}Extras @{ub} (Flags)

  - With the checkboxes you can control WBW's behavior:

    - @{b}All player buttons@{ub}: If this mode is on, the player
      window is opened with three buttons: [ok], [pass] and [take back].
      If it's off, only the 'ok' button will appear.
      (@{i} default: on @{ui})

    - @{b}Show opponents letters@{ub}: If you want to get a smaller
      players window, turn this mode off. This means that the computer
      player's letters are hidden constantly.
      (@{i} default: on @{ui})

    - @{b}All graphics & animations@{ub}: If this mode is on
      most requesters show little images. You may turn this off
      to save memory or space on the screen.
      (@{i} default: on @{ui})

    - @{b}Open all windows at start@{ub}: If this mode is on,
      WBW opens all three windows (players data, letters and board)
      at start.
      (@{i} default: off @{ui})

    - @{b}Print points on letters@{ub}: If you use a very small graphic
      set (e.g. 'mini.des'), the numbers on the letters are nearly
      unreadable (with 'mini.des' they're displayed in binary code). So
      turn them off, if you want.
      (@{i} default: on @{ui})

 @{b}Screenmode @{ub}

  - If you want to play WBW on an own screen, click on @{b}"Select"@{ub}.
    To use the workbench screen, click on @{b}"Use Workbench"@{ub}.

    WBW will have problems if you select a small screen but
    large fonts or graphics. See @{"Problems with Prefs" link emergency} for
    more information. 

 @{b}Learning mode  @{ub}

  - You can choose among:

    - @{b}Always learn@{ub}: Which means that all words you place on the
      board, which are not part of the vocabulary at the moment, are
      added to it.

    - @{b}Ask to learn@{ub}: Which means that will a requester appears for 
      each new word and you can select, if it should be added or not.

    - @{b}Never learn@{ub}: No words will be added to the vocabulary.

 @{b}Window positions@{ub}

  - If you select 'Save&Use' all preferences and the window positions
    will be saved.

@endnode

@node emergency "Problems with the preferences"

  @{b}Problems with preferences@{ub}

  ... @{u}Problems@{uu} ...

  As mentioned above, you can select screenmodes, fonts and graphics
  that don't harmonize.

  - @{b}Fonts@{ub} do not affect the main window dimensions, but all 
    other window sizes.

  - @{b}Graphics sizes@{ub} affect all windows displaying letters.

  You may reduce these effects if you turn @{i}All graphics
  and animations, show opponents letters,@{ui} and  @{i}all player 
  buttons@{ui} (see 'Extras' in @{"display prefs" link prefs}) off. This may 
  reduce the sizes of the windows.

  ... @{u}Emergency-Prefs@{uu} ...

  If WBW is not able to open it's windows, a requester will appear. You
  may quit WBW then or try it with 'emergency-prefs' this means that
  WBW restarts with the following settings:

     @{i}Graphics file: DES/mini.des@{ui}      - These means a letter size 
     of 12x12 pixel and, resulting, a board size of 180x180 pixel. See
     @{"graphic files" link graphics} for more information.

     @{i}Screenmode:    Hi-Res interlaced@{ui} - A (flickering) screen of
     640x512 pixel, which hopefully can be displayed on all systems.

     @{i}Fonts:         Topaz (8 pixel)@{ui}   - WBW chooses this font, 
     because it's allways available. There could be fonts installed on your 
     system that would be more suitable, but WBW can't depend on them.

  With this settings WBW should be able to open it's windows, especially
  the preferences requester. Then you may change the settings to your
  prefered. 
    
@endnode

@node graphics "Graphic-files"

  @{b}New file format@{ub}

  WBWort uses an own format for graphic files now, which includes
  all bitmaps (board, letters, points and preview). New graphic files
  will be released separatly from the main archive.

  @{b}Do it yourself...@{ub}

  You can participate in WBW's development and draw your own
  graphic files. There's an IFF-Picture with an example and instructions
  in the archive, named: @{"Docs/DoItYourself.iff" link DoItyourself.iff/main}.

  At the moment, WBW uses the MagicWB colors. This means an 8 color
  palette as used in the example.

  There are other ways to participate, too: See chapter @{"participation" link parti}.

  @{b}New graphic files@{ub}

  New designs for WBWort will be released separatly from the main archive
  in the AMINET and my support mailbox @{"BLUESTAR AMIGA" link "bluestar"}.
 
@endnode

@node parti "Participation"

  @{b}Participation@{ub}

  1. @{u}Draw your own graphic files@{uu} :

    See chapter @{"graphic files" link graphics} for more information.

  2. @{u}Add your own language@{uu} :

    If want a version using your own language, please write a
    postcard or an e-mail with the number of letters used in your 
    local scrabble (like 5 of `a`, 2 of `b` etc.) and the points 
    they score. 

  3. @{u}Make an own vocabulary@{uu} :

    I'm allways interested in new vocabulary files. Vocabularies
    grow while playing and the new VocEd makes it possible to
    mix these files. This means, if you send me your vocabulary
    I can add the new words to the 'official' vocabulary file.

  4. @{u}Translate WBWort@{uu} :

    If you want to localize WBW for your own language, contact
    me via e-mail. I'll send you a ct-file. 

  @{b}Contact:@{ub}

  Best (and cheapest) way to exchange these files is via e-mail.
 
  My address ---> @{"Author" link autho}.

  If there's use for the files you send, you will get a free keyfile
  and/or the next update.

@endnode

